                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14358.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from Carothers, Irapuato: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>General Villa has ordered authorities at Mexicali to abstain from
                            collecting the two dollars tax from Chinese subjects.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
